@GiudGiud Sorry for the confusion. I edited the expression. The integral is part of another integral (also over the whole domain) which is with dx.
Yes, the integral is over the whole volume.
Yes, the "x" is the current location. So, this integral has to be calculated at each quadrature point ("x") for the whole volume.

looking at the code, it fails in this last line
  const auto grain_num = _ebsd_reader.getGrainNum();
  _euler_angle.resize(grain_num);
  _quat_angle.resize(grain_num);

  // Get Euler Angle of Orientation
  for (const auto i : make_range(grain_num))
  {
    auto grain_id = _ebsd_reader.getFeatureID(i);
    _euler_angle[grain_id] = _ebsd_reader.getEulerAngles(i);

you can debug further by printing the size of the arrays.
My guess is that there are more grains specified in the reader than there are Euler angles specified. So we are reading out of bounds
